    • Field Detail

      • FACE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FACE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains face. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of face image is enabled (see setDisplayFaceImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains signature. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of signature image is enabled (see setDisplaySignatureImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setDisplayFullDocumentImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • CREATOR

      • setDisplaySignatureImage

        public void setDisplaySignatureImage(boolean displaySignatureImage)
        Sets whether signature image from passport should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        displaySignatureImage - whether signature image should be sent to MetadataListener.

      • shouldDisplaySignatureImage

        public boolean shouldDisplaySignatureImage()
        Returns whether sending of signature image from passport to MetadataListener is enabled.
        Returns:
        whether sending of signature image from passport to MetadataListener is enabled.
